div.p:
So that the words, you see, divide themselues into two Generall Parts;


An Exhortation,


And a Motiue to induce thereunto.

Concerning which,
                  Branch 1. it shall not be amisse to enquire;
                  Observ. 2.


1. What Kingdome this is;
                        Points 3.


2. Wherein it consisteth;
                        Point 1.


3. Why it is so termed.


Now further this Kingdome is called the Kingdome of God;
                  Point 3. Reasons 4. Reason 1. Reason 2. Reason 3. Reason 4.


1. Because 
                        Matth. 20.23. he hath prepared it;

2. Because 
                        Luke 12.32. he conferreth and bestoweth it;

3. Because 
                        Apoc. 4.10. of and under him we hold it;

4. Because 
                        Apoc. 20.6. with him wee reigne in it; for from him we receive it, and together with him we reigne in it.


                  Questions 3.Now concerning this Righteousnesse, three Questions would be discussed;


1. What is meant by Righteousnesse here;

2. Why it is called the Righteousnesse of God;

3. Why no part in this Kingdome can be had without it.
